modules.description: Encodes and decodes CBOR data items into sequences of signals, handling both fixed and indefinite-length structures. Processes integers larger than 8 bytes as bignums and supports streaming large data. Converts between signals and byte sequences for serialization and deserialization.

Encodes and decodes CBOR data items using streaming and lazy evaluation, handling major types such as integers, floats, strings, and arrays. It works with OCaml's native types like int, float, string, list, and option, as well as custom types via user-defined serializers. Use cases include parsing network protocols, serializing configuration data, and processing large binary files efficiently.

Encodes and decodes CBOR data items, handling fixed and indefinite-length structures, with support for bignums and streaming. Converts between signals and byte sequences for serialization and deserialization. Provides types for integers, floats, strings, arrays, maps, and tags. Examples include serializing a large integer to a byte stream or parsing a CBOR-encoded array from a network buffer.
